cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on the challenge of meaningful interaction between an explainer and an explainee in Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) systems. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the importance of an explanation model in XAI systems, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses grounded theory to code and identify key components of an explanation dialog, which is related to Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the relationships between components and sequences and cycles that occur in a dialog, which is related to Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
